# Ops Task Builder

- Read `mm_calendar/00_GUIDELINES_ITAY.md`, `mm_calendar/ops_board_schema.md`, `mm_calendar/ops_task_construction.md`, and `mm_calendar/documentation/ops_task_refs/README.md` first.
- Source board: `Operation - Monetization` (`2109172490`); `57490550` is its view ID. Production tasks belong as subitems under the exact `YYYY-MM-DD` day parent.
- Build only from an approved calendar day and only when Itay explicitly requests it. Dry-run is the default; live writing requires explicit `--commit`.
- The MM calendar Name is authoritative over a conflicting Description. Keep missing execution details as `TBD - owner required`; never infer rewards, segments, parameters, IDs, owners, files, or links.
- Connect every Ops subitem's `MM calendar` relation (`board_relation_mkzvrve9`) to its exact `source_mm_item_id`. Verify with `BoardRelationValue.linked_items`; Monday's generic relation `text`/`value` fields may stay null even when the link exists.
- Historical execution references are limited to the 3 calendar months before the target date. Use the newest matching promo/variant first; never copy older tasks when no recent precedent exists.
- `Reuse` requires a verified recent Ops source: record its date/item ID, reused scope, and current delta. The MM Creative Label alone is not proof of operational reuse.
- **Standard offers** (not Daily Deal): `Segment` → `Prizes` → `Pricing`, prefixed with `Reset at 00:00 UTC`. **X2 Extreme Stamp:** `Segment` only, then **`don't forget UI`**. **MGAP** (variant promos): `Segment` → `Variant`, then UI reminder (`don't forget UI` or `Make sure to set UI for both Extreme + Epic` when both tiers apply). **X2 GGS:** excluded from task generation (calendar amplifier); if a task is ever created, Description includes `don't forget UI` + timer on the inapp (historical Ops voice). **Rolling Offer:** `Segment` → `Pricing` → `Denoms:` with **`Cycle N:`** headers then numbered denoms. **Other variant promos** (Shiny Show, Golden Spin, Dice, LBP/Lotto): `Segment` → `Variant`. **Sales:** `Currency` → PU/PRAS amounts — **coupons** = flat `<PU%>` / `<PRAS%>` (no store|offers); **sales** = store|offers + PRAS bonus math (+20 gems / +25 coins). **ADS:** `Segment` → `Prizes` only (no Pricing). **RLAP:** `Trigger: Eligible offers: …` + segmented `Prize` lines (no Pricing). **Other promos:** `Segment` → optional `Trigger` → `Prize`.
- **Times per player:** main offers + Piggy → `Once`; **Win Master** → `Once`; Daily Deal → `Multiple` unless MM overrides; **leave blank** for **machine full launch**, Short Term / Mid Term / Season (and similar seasonals). **Spinner Clash** → `Multiple` (recent Ops precedent). Never repeat in Description.
- Duplicate only the newest exact promo/variant inside the valid three-month window. If only a generic template exists, name its template group and keep unsupported fields as TBD; never present it as verified reuse.
- August Promo Time is 11:00 UTC. A calendar date range is inclusive and ends at 11:00 UTC on the following day after its final date.
- Never fill `Operation Status` (`dup__of_m_m_status1`); Ops owns it. The agent owns and may set only `M&M Status`.
- Put Once/Multiple only in the dedicated `Times per player` column; never repeat it in Description.
- Start/End date columns must include clock time. Standard promo: 11:00 UTC to next-day 11:00 UTC; time-limited/Night Plan tasks use their exact approved hours. Time-limited promos without MM clocks: stable pick among 14:00 / 16:00 / 17:00 / 21:00 UTC (hash of day + MM item id), duration from MM text or default 1h; reflect start in subitem title (`HH:MM UTC - …`).
- Do not put production dates, start/end times, reset times, or date ranges in Description. Keep scheduling only in the Start/End date columns. The Ops board renders API date-times at UTC+3, so offset API values by -3 hours to make the visible Monday clock equal the intended UTC schedule.
- Never put repo paths, Nivi prize-table filenames, `Full tables: …`, or Collector's Album phase boilerplate in Description; composer strips these via `finalize_ops_description()` in `scripts/ops_description.py`.
- Generate tasks only when Ops must configure/open/schedule/award/target/publish/QA/close something. Exclude calendar-only rows that need no config (Status Boost, Shiny Collection comms, X2 Extreme Stamp, X2 GGS, Clan-Dash).
- Ace Heist keeps its linear three-mission progression flow, but Ace Heist and PYP mission content/values must come from the exact current Monday row. Never default to historical mission values; omit Trigger and flag missing information when the row has no missions.
- Golden Spin is a coin-value feature, never a Gems feature. Keep the classification internal and do not explain it in Description.
- A calendar day containing Night Plan Lotto peak + LBP always creates two separate Ops tasks under that day's parent. Each visibly runs on the following date from 00:00 through 11:00 and uses M&M Status `Night Plan` (for example, parent 2026-08-01 → production window 2026-08-02 00:00–11:00).
- Choose the most specific `M&M Status` from the current handoff state (`Night Plan`, `Missing MCP`, `Missing art`, `Missing Art+Config`, `Missing Config`, `Missing List`, `Missing Test Groups`, `Waiting for economy`, `More Info required`, or `MM Work in Progress`). When **config/MCP is ready** and Description is complete, use **`Waiting for MM Approval`** (not `M&M Completed`). Do **not** use `More Info required` only because MM **Description** is empty when **Name** (+ composer) already supplies prizes/triggers (DD, Win Master, machine launch, Spinner Clash). Night Plan tasks use `Night Plan`. Never claim successful Ops/QA execution in M&M Status.
- **Machine full launch** (`Event` / name contains machine + launch): Description = Main Inapp + Figz/Winovate playlist + New Machines DF checklist (see `ops_task_construction.md`); match Sweet Ambrosia / Rich's Riches Ops precedents.
- **Rolling Offer** Description: blank line between each `Cycle N:` block.
- One day at a time. Match within that day by normalized task name. Add/update only; never delete, move, archive, comment, attach, relate, or assign unless explicitly authorized.
- When only existing descriptions are approved for repair, use `--commit --update-existing --description-only`; it must update only `long_text` and refuse missing tasks.
- If the day parent is missing, stop unless Itay explicitly authorized creating it. Show the full proposed payload and every TBD before writing.
